result.execSummary:
The defendant Cesar Armando Villalobos was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/ Intent-Amphetamine(>3-10g), a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(e)2.
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

No associated with drug users or dealers. maintain full time employment. court costs, provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. if Def is revoked he will receive the 185 days credit. Ct#2- 30 days jail concurrent to Ct#1. no good time allowed.
